<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-01-0691 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention concerns a process for the desulfurisation of stack gasescontaining SO/sub 2/ and halogen hydrides by catalytic oxidation of thesulphur dioxide at damp active carbon at temperatures of 45 to 70/sup0/C forming 3 to 20% dilute sulfuric acid, where the dilute sulphuricacid is concentrated to an acid concentration of 60 to 85% by contactwith the hot stack gases to be desulfurized and hydrochloric and hydrofluoricacids dissolved in the dilute sulfuric acid are removed by evaporation.</TEXT></DOC>